Reasoning: The paper discusses an algorithmic problem for symbolic computation related to polynomials and semi-algebraic domains, which suggests it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of semi-definite programming and its applications to engineering sciences, program verification, and cyber-physical systems suggest it could belong to cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Computer Algebra). The mention of hybrid symbolic-numeric algorithms suggests it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of polynomial constraints and the decision problem suggest it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the mention of cyber-physical systems and program verification suggests it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
